  "title": "Technical Officer (Electrical)",
  "description": "<p>Your Role:</p><p>• Carry out routine and maintenance programme of all electrical equipment</p><p>• Perform rectification of faults on the electrical systems</p><p>• Assisting engineers in carrying out switching and isolation of low voltage equipment</p><p>• Monitoring and control of contract workers to ensure compliance with technical specifications, code of practice, scope to work and to enforce safety regulations</p><p>• Inspections and acceptance of purchased materials and contract spares</p><p>• Updating of maintenance records</p><p>• Co-ordination of work with other sections</p><p>• Repairing faulty electrical instruments and tools</p><p>• Reporting unsafe conditions/ near miss incidents for rectification</p><p><br />Your Profile:</p><p>• Minimum Diploma in Electrical Engineering or equivalent</p><p>• 5 years of relevant working experience in maintenance electrical in power or process plants environment</p><p>• Good working attitude, Team player</p><p>• The offered job grade/designation will be based on candidate’s experience, competencies and skillsets</p>",
